One of the downsides to subscriptions inside subscriptions is that it is really challenging to correctly unsubscribe from both. Consider instead using higher order mapping operators.

Something like this:

      selectedProductSuppliers$ = this.selectedProduct$
        .pipe(
          filter(selectedProduct =&gt; Boolean(selectedProduct)),
          switchMap(selectedProduct =&gt;
            forkJoin(selectedProduct.supplierIds.map(supplierId =&gt; this.http.get&lt;Supplier&gt;(`${this.suppliersUrl}/${supplierId}`)))
          )
        );

When the first Observable (this.selectedProduct$) emits, it filters out any nulls (no product was selected). Then it uses switchMap (a higher-order mapping operator) to handle the inner subscription.

So your code would look something more like this:

    getUsersDataObs().pipe(
       switchMap(data =&gt; sendMailObs(data))
    )
    .subscribe()

